entry.title: vietnamese input engine: Reactivate to change options instead of OnFocus
entry.content:
The previous approach used the deperecated OnFocus settingsptr object to

change the options. This had the unintended sideeffect of not sending an

onfocus event to the vk which was causing issues with handwriting commit

text.



This change fixes the handwriting issue, while also preserving the

behaviour of options changes causing intended effect on IME without

requiring switching IMEs.

entry.title: Add speech recognition option to skip continuously empty audio
entry.content:
Websites may produce audio streams consisting of nothing but zeroes. We

can improve performance by catching this special case before passing the

audio on to the speech recognition engine.



This CL adds an option to do this to SpeechRecognitionOptions.



The implementation waits for 10 seconds of empty (i.e. all-zero) audio

before skipping subsequent empty audio packets, because brief periods of

empty audio can be meaningful input to the speech recognition engine.

entry.title: Fix clipped text under fractional display scaling
entry.content:
Previously, Canvas::DrawStringRect() clipped text within a given

bounding rectangle. When the canvas was scaled fractionally, the

boundary of this rectangle might not align perfectly with pixels,

leading to unintended clipping of pixels on the boundary.

dip if the canvas is scaled.

entry.content:
Instead of hiding the toggle if the save and fill payment methods toggle

is off, or if the device does not have biometric or screen lock

authentication available, the most recent UX alignment is we want to

show a disabled toggle.



This CL ensures that the toggle is disabled in the following cases:

1) The "Save and fill payment methods" toggle is turned off.

device.



It also removes the special handling of the following case:

1) If the re-auth toggle was previously turned on, but there is no

device auth available on the device. Instead, if one of the 2 conditions

above for the toggle to be disabled are triggered, the toggle will be

disabled but it will display the correct value based on whether it was

on or off.

entry.title: multi-display: Store restore bounds in parent in PersistentWindowInfo
entry.content:
Stores the window's restore bounds in parent instead of restore

bounds in screen to PersistentWindowInfo. Then later it can be

used to get the window's restore bounds in screen based on updated

displays' layout.



The old method to adjust the window's restore bounds in screen

based on the display origin offset actually has a wrong assumption.

It requires the display bounds stored inside PersistentWindowInfo

are the value before display removal happens, but actually inside

`OnDisplayRemoved` where we create the PersistentWindowInfo, the

displays' layout already changes, which means the display bounds

we get at that point are the value after display removal happens.



Bug: b/252542445

entry.title: Exclude scrollbar autoscroll animation from ongoing_scroll_animation
entry.content:
ongoing_scroll_animation is used to determine when

WidgetInputHandler::WaitForInputProcessed should run its callback: it

won't be run until ongoing_scroll_animation is false. The only caller

of WaitForInputProcessed is SyntheticGestureController, which uses it

when triggering a sequence of gesture events, to ensure that each

event is fully processed before the next event is sent.



Prior to this patch, if a synthetic pointer down event falls on a

scrollbar button, then WaitForInputProcessed would not invoke its

callback until the resulting scroll animation finished, i.e., when the

beginning or end of the scroll node's content was reached. This

happens because the pointer down event initiates a scroll animation

(called an "autoscroll" animation) that continues until either a pointer

up event is received, or the end of the scrolling region is reached.



In practice, that's not the desired behavior -- it's actually impossible

to synthetically click a scrollbar button once to scroll by a single

increment, because the pointer up event will be blocked until the

autoscroll animation ends by other means (i.e, the end is reached).

crbug.com/1447868 explains why this hasn't caused more problems.



With this change, WaitForInputProcessed will only wait until

there is no running non-autoscroll animation; it will ignore the

state of autoscroll animations.

entry.title: [omnibox][chrome://omnibox] Improve 'click to expand' trigger.
entry.content:
In chrome://omnibox, clicking on suggestion rows expands their height to

make their contents more readable. This doesn't happen when the user is

trying to select text from the page (e.g. to copy), since it would mess

up the selection.



Currently, the logic to avoid expansion when selecting text checks if

the mouse moved between the mouse-down and mouse-up events. This has a

lot of false positives, because the mouse often moves a pixel or 2 when

clicking. So the user often has to click multiple times before the row

expands, which is annoying.



This CL changes the logic: it avoids expansion when there is actual text

selected.



This isn't foolproof either: unselecting text by clicking inside the

previous selection will send the 'click' event before selection is

cleared, causing the logic to not realize the selection is being removed

and the height expansion to not occur. But it seems much better than the

existing trigger.

entry.title: [omnibox][ml] Add feature param to increase provider limits to 10.
entry.content:
This CL adds a feature param to override the max matches by provider

limit when ML scoring is enabled. It also adds a feature variant

that sets the URL providers (HQP, HUP, Bookmark, shortcut, and fuzzy

history) max matches to 10.



This allows us to pass more suggestions to be re-scored by the model,

increasing the likelihood of making an impact without making as big of

a performance regression as re-scoring all possible candidates

(unlimited suggestions). The IncreaseNumCandidates param/variant is

also re-named to UnlimitedNumCandidates.



Bug: 1405555
